Mother bears make a woofing sound to warn cubs of  
danger and will call them with a whimper. 
 
Except for females with cubs, black bears are fairly  
solitary. In general, black bears avoid humans and  
are not aggressive except when feeding, injured, or  
protecting their young or themselves. However, these  
bears can do serious damage to cornfields and  
honeybee hives and may become a problem around  
campgrounds if food is left within their reach. In  
some cases, black bears have seriously hurt and even  
killed people who feed them. 
 
